All cockpit crew are kindly requested to comply with the following guidelines to enhance fuel management and optimize consumption analysis:
1.	Flight Level Planning:
Plan the Operational Flight Plan (OFP) for FL290–FL320, except for routes under 50 minutes flight time.
2.	Cruise Speed:
Planned cruising Mach in the OFP should be Mach 0.72 unless operational reasons dictate otherwise.
3.	Taxi Fuel:
Plan 250 lbs taxi fuel in the OFP, except OIII (Tehran Mehrabad) and OIIM (Mashhad) where 350 lbs applies.
4.	Bleed Configuration for Takeoff:
Use APU bleed for Pack 1 and Engine 2 bleed for Pack 2 up to acceleration altitude.
5.	Climb Mode:
Use FLC mode after acceleration altitude unless safety requires otherwise.
6.	Cruise Parameter Cross-Check:
The Captain must ensure FMS data matches the OFP for:
o	Cruising altitude
o	ISA deviation
o	Cruise wind
o	Cruising Mach number
Deviation from the OFP is only acceptable for flight safety.
7.	Fuel-on-Board Entry in OFP:
Calculate actual fuel on board as:
Total fuel before engine start – total fuel indicated on the FUEL MFD page after start-up.
Ignore the “fuel used” value on the MFD.
', 'ODB', 'Vahid', '+989123379445', 'Full-Time', 'seraj.m', 2.0, 'Operational Fuel Management and Flight Planning Guidelines updated', 'TEHR', 2.0, NULL, 2.0, 10027.0, '', 'Bozorgnia');
