INSERT INTO `report_45_2025_08_08` (`DaysUnAcknowledged`, `EmailAddress`, `RequiresAction`, `BaseName`, `URL`, `DeleteOnAck`, `AlertStatusName`, `ModifiedAt`, `CreatedAt`, `PersonnelID`, `DepartmentName`, `PhoneNo`, `AlertBody`, `AlertCategoryName`, `FirstName`, `MobileNo`, `EmploymentText`, `CreatedBy`, `DepartmentID`, `AlertTitle`, `BaseShortName`, `AlertStatus`, `ModifiedBy`, `BaseID`, `AlertID`, `FaxNo`, `LastName`) VALUES (53, 'Bozorgnia.v@Raimonairways.ir;Bozorgnia.v@Raimonairways.net', 0, 'Tehran', '~/Controls/GetFile.ashx?Type=Document&ID=15128', 0, 'Critical', NULL, '2025-08-23T16:22:08.323', 34.0, 'Pilot', '', '1. Objective
To ensure timely preparation for subsequent flights, reduce delays, and provide accurate operational information to all relevant departments.

2. Applicability
This procedure applies to all cockpit crew members upon completion of each flight and prior to commencement of the next duty sector.

3. Responsibilities

The Commander (PIC) has overall responsibility for ensuring that all required documentation and tasks are completed.

The First Officer supports the PIC in completing documentation and system setup.

4. Procedure
Within 10 minutes after landing and parking at the gate/stand, the cockpit crew shall complete the following tasks:

Flight Documentation:

File and complete the previous Operational Flight Plan (OFP).

File and complete the Journey Log.

File and complete the Aircraft Technical Log (ATL) and/or Electronic Technical Log (ETL) as applicable.

EFB Preparation:

Synchronization of data (JEP FD, GURU 2).

Updating performance, weather, NOTAMs, and route packages.

Ensuring sufficient battery power and backup availability (direct charging the iPad more than 70%).

Operational Coordination:

Provide required trip/flight information to the Loadmaster (passenger figures, expected cargo/fuel balance, special loads).

Confirm and input the fuel requirement for the next sector, based on OFP and PIC review.

Next Flight Acceptance:

If all conditions are acceptable, the PIC shall declare acceptance of the next flight.

The PIC may then issue the boarding authorization to the Flight Purser to commence passenger boarding.

5. Notes

Boarding shall not commence until the PIC has reviewed and approved the OFP, ATL/ETL status, and fuel figures.

Coordination with OCC/Dispatch must be maintained in case of fuel changes, MEL restrictions, or operational concerns.

