INSERT INTO `report_45_2025_08_08` (`DaysUnAcknowledged`, `EmailAddress`, `RequiresAction`, `BaseName`, `URL`, `DeleteOnAck`, `AlertStatusName`, `ModifiedAt`, `CreatedAt`, `PersonnelID`, `DepartmentName`, `PhoneNo`, `AlertBody`, `AlertCategoryName`, `FirstName`, `MobileNo`, `EmploymentText`, `CreatedBy`, `DepartmentID`, `AlertTitle`, `BaseShortName`, `AlertStatus`, `ModifiedBy`, `BaseID`, `AlertID`, `FaxNo`, `LastName`) VALUES (49, 'Bozorgnia.v@Raimonairways.ir;Bozorgnia.v@Raimonairways.net', 0, 'Tehran', '~/Controls/GetFile.ashx?Type=Document&ID=15133', 0, 'Caution', NULL, '2025-08-27T11:14:42.437', 34.0, 'Pilot', '', '
Commencement & Continuation of Approach
•	The Commander or delegated pilot may commence an instrument approach regardless of reported RVR/VIS.
•	If reported RVR/VIS < applicable minimum, approach shall not be continued:
• Below 1,000 ft above the aerodrome, or
• Into the final approach segment if DA/H or MDA/H > 1,000 ft above aerodrome.
•	If no RVR is available, and reported VIS < minimum but Converted Meteorological Visibility (CMV) = minimum, approach may continue to DA/H or MDA/H.
•	If RVR/VIS deteriorates after passing 1,000 ft AAL or entering FAS, approach may continue, subject to normal visual reference requirements at DA/H.
•	Approach may be continued below DA/H or MDA/H and landing completed if adequate visual references are established and maintained.
•	Minimum RVR for continuation:
(a) Touchdown RVR is controlling.
(b) If touchdown RVR not reported ? midpoint RVR is controlling.
Visual References for NPA, APV & CAT I
At DA/H or MDA/H, pilots must have:
•	VASI/PAPI (mandatory for NPA at night, optional by day, CAT I, or RNP Baro VNAV).
•	Plus at least one of the following distinctly visible and identifiable references:
• Threshold
• Threshold markings
• Threshold lights
• Threshold identification lights
• Touchdown zone or markings
• Touchdown zone lights
• Runway/FATO edge lights
•	Note: Approach lighting alone is not sufficient for NPA.
Important: State-specific minima or visual reference requirements may be more restrictive (refer to Jeppesen Country Rules, Regulations, and AIP).

', 'ODB', 'Vahid', '+989123379445', 'Full-Time', 'seraj.m', 2.0, 'Commencement & Continuation of Approach / Visual Reference Requirements updated', 'TEHR', 2.0, NULL, 2.0, 10034.0, '', 'Bozorgnia');
INSERT INTO `report_45_2025_08_08` (`DaysUnAcknowledged`, `EmailAddress`, `RequiresAction`, `BaseName`, `URL`, `DeleteOnAck`, `AlertStatusName`, `ModifiedAt`, `CreatedAt`, `PersonnelID`, `DepartmentName`, `PhoneNo`, `AlertBody`, `AlertCategoryName`, `FirstName`, `MobileNo`, `EmploymentText`, `CreatedBy`, `DepartmentID`, `AlertTitle`, `BaseShortName`, `AlertStatus`, `ModifiedBy`, `BaseID`, `AlertID`, `FaxNo`, `LastName`) VALUES (49, 'Bozorgnia.v@Raimonairways.ir;Bozorgnia.v@Raimonairways.net', 0, 'Tehran', '~/Controls/GetFile.ashx?Type=Document&ID=15134', 0, 'Caution', NULL, '2025-08-27T11:33:24.55', 34.0, 'Pilot', '', '
En-route Fuel Check
•	Crews must monitor flight time and fuel burn vs. OFP trends.
•	Fuel checks shall be performed every 30 minutes, recording fuel used and remaining.
•	Fuel remaining must be compared with required fuel to complete the flight.
•	On sectors >90 minutes, record fuel quantities and estimated destination fuel at intervals not exceeding 1 hour, overhead/abeam suitable waypoints.
•	If fuel remaining is close to minima, options include:
• Adjusting speed
• Requesting direct routing
• Changing flight level
• Selecting closer alternate aerodrome
•	If sufficient fuel cannot be ensured ? Land and refuel.
•	ERA procedures and adverse conditions may temporarily allow negative balance vs. minimum requirement; caution and early communication with dispatch/ground handling are required.
Inflight Fuel Management Policy & Procedures
•	PIC must ensure regular fuel checks throughout flight.
•	Compare actual vs. planned consumption.
•	Confirm usable fuel is sufficient for flight completion.
•	Determine expected usable fuel on arrival at destination.
•	Ensure expected usable fuel on arrival is not less than:
• Alternate fuel + Final Reserve Fuel; OR
• Final Reserve Fuel (if no alternate is required).
If Expected Fuel < Required Minima
•	PIC shall request ATC delay information.
•	Consider operational/traffic conditions at destination and alternates.
•	Divert if needed to ensure safe landing with = Final Reserve Fuel.
•	Declare emergency if predicted landing fuel < Final Reserve Fuel at nearest adequate aerodrome.

', 'ODB', 'Vahid', '+989123379445', 'Full-Time', 'seraj.m', 2.0, 'En-route Fuel Check & Inflight Fuel Management Policy updated', 'TEHR', 2.0, NULL, 2.0, 10035.0, '', 'Bozorgnia');
