INSERT INTO `report_45_2025_08_08` (`DaysUnAcknowledged`, `EmailAddress`, `RequiresAction`, `BaseName`, `URL`, `DeleteOnAck`, `AlertStatusName`, `ModifiedAt`, `CreatedAt`, `PersonnelID`, `DepartmentName`, `PhoneNo`, `AlertBody`, `AlertCategoryName`, `FirstName`, `MobileNo`, `EmploymentText`, `CreatedBy`, `DepartmentID`, `AlertTitle`, `BaseShortName`, `AlertStatus`, `ModifiedBy`, `BaseID`, `AlertID`, `FaxNo`, `LastName`) VALUES (6, 'asadi.n@raimonairways.net;asadi.n@raimonairways.ir', 0, 'Tehran', '~/Controls/GetFile.ashx?Type=Document&ID=4586', 0, 'Critical', NULL, '2025-10-09T08:56:37.183', 176.0, 'Flight Operation Officer', '', 'Action required

Before completing Trip Information and handing it to Ground Ops, calculate all four limiting takeoff weights and determine RTOW:

MSTOW (AFM structural limit).

PLTOW (performance-limited TOW via GURU2 considering runway length/gradient, temperature, pressure, wind, obstacles, runway surface, MEL/CDL, etc.).

TOW based on MLW = MSLW + Trip Fuel (ensure planned landing weight at destination/alternate = MLW).

TOW based on MZFW = MZFW + T/O Fuel (ensure ZFW = MZFW).

RTOW = min{MSTOW, PLTOW, MLW-based TOW, MZFW-based TOW}. 



Verify the operational limit:

ATOW (Actual TOW) = RTOW is mandatory.

ATOW = DOW + Pax Weight + Cargo + T/O Fuel. 



If capacity remains, compute admissible extra passengers:

Extra PAX = (RTOW - ATOW) / 230 lb per pax (standard assumption).

Any boarding above the original plan is permitted only after completing and documenting these calculations. 



Re-compute if inputs change:

Runway, wind, QNH, MEL/CDL, temperature, anti-ice, flap, or surface condition changes require a fresh PLTOW/RTOW check. 



Documentation & accountability:

The PIC is responsible for accuracy of calculations.

Attach/save the calculation sheet with the OFP for record-keeping. 


Reference aircraft limits (extract):
EP-NEA/EP-NEB — MSTOW 46,275 lb; MSLW 41,226 lb; MZFW 37,698 lb.
EP-NEC — MSTOW 48,501 lb; MSLW 42,549 lb; MZFW 39,462 lb. ', 'ODB', 'Naser', '', 'Full-Time', 'seraj.m', 4.0, 'EXTRA PAX Calculation Procedure for Cold-Weather Performance Gain.', 'TEHR', 1.0, NULL, 2.0, 20043.0, '', 'Asadi');
